@startuml
title Indirect flow across a shared dataset, blocked by the *-property (A6)
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequence {
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FDEEEE
  ParticipantBorderColor #B54A4A
  ActorBackgroundColor #FDEEEE
  ActorBorderColor #B54A4A
  LifeLineBorderColor #B54A4A
}

actor "User A" as A
actor "User B" as B
database "Oil Company A" as OA
database "Bank A\n(shared, neutral)" as BA
database "Oil Company B" as OB

A -> OA : read (allowed)
A -> BA : write Oil A secrets
note right of BA
  Without *-property this write
  is permitted by A2 alone
end note
B -> BA : read
B --> OB : leak reaches
note over A, OB
  *-property (A6): A may read Oil A
  (a different dataset, unsanitized),
  so the write to Bank A is DENIED.
  T4: unsanitized info stays in its
  own dataset; sanitized info flows.
end note
@enduml
